Our doll looking fresh post her Prp treatment 🌟

Platelet Rich Plasma (PRP) Therapy is a very natural cosmetic skin rejuvenation treatment, otherwise known as the “Vampire” lift. uses your own blood to harvest concentrated plasma, which is rich in platelets. This treatment uses your own ‘enriched’ plasma as an advanced anti-aging and healing treatment delivered to the skin in a process similar to mesotherapy.  The secret lies in extracting and increasing the autological factors in your blood.  These autological factors are what your body needs to heal itself. PRP Therapy re-activates the autological factors in your body’s repair system getting your skin to regenerate more efficiently.
 
Using PRP Therapy as an anti-aging facial treatment is highly effective.  This natural and safe treatment uses your own blood, which is extracted and enriched (with no chemicals or additives) in an easy and comfortable process and is then re-injected into your face through several ‘meso-type’ tiny injections.  The benefits of this approach are the natural and self-healing effects of regenerated skin, improved skin vitality, improved sun damaged skin, and better skin hydration.

What is Hair PRP?

Hair PRP (Platelet-Rich Plasma) is a hair restoration treatment that involves using a patient's own blood to promote hair growth. The process involves drawing a small amount of blood, processing it to concentrate the platelets, and then injecting the concentrated plasma back into the scalp. The platelets contain growth factors that help to promote the growth and health of hair follicles. This treatment has been used to help individuals both men and women who are experiencing hair thinning or hair loss.

Do you want clear, glowing & healthy skin? 

Regular trips to the clinic can definitely help in maintaining your skin health. Here are some tips to make the most of your visits and ensure proper skincare:

Establish a regular skincare routine:
Consistency is key. Develop a daily skincare routine that includes cleansing, moisturizing, and protecting your skin from the sun. Our practitioners can help you choose the right products tailored to your needs.

Protect yourself from the sun:
Sunscreen is essential to protect your skin from harmful UV rays. Apply sunscreen with a minimum SPF of 30, even on cloudy days, and reapply every few hours when exposed to the sun.

Hydrate and nourish your skin: Drink plenty of water to keep your skin hydrated and follow a healthy diet rich in fruits, vegetables, and essential fatty acids. These nutrients can help improve your skin's overall health and appearance.

Adopt a healthy lifestyle: Good overall health reflects on your skin. Get enough sleep, manage stress levels, exercise regularly, and avoid habits like smoking or excessive alcohol consumption that can harm your skin's health.

Remember, our advice is your best resource for personalized guidance and treatment options. By following the steps to taking care of your skin daily, you can maintain its health and vitality.

CARBON LASER TREATMENT 
——————————————————

⏰ approx. 45mins

Also known as a “Hollywood Facial” or a “China Doll” treatment, this carbon laser treatment reduces the appearance of marks, imperfections and fine lines / wrinkles and improves the firmness and overall appearance of the skin. It is a great anti-ageing treatment for the face, neck, back, hands and chest.

A layer of liquid carbon is applied to the skin, where it penetrates deep into the pores. 
Laser light is highly attracted to the carbon particles. When the laser is passed over the area, it destroys the carbon, taking dead skin cells, contaminants and oil with it.

Carbon Laser, sometimes known as carbon peel, is an innovative laser treatment that is absolutely painless and promises a minimal to zero downtime.

To be considered for lip fillers, you should:

You might want to enlarge the size of your lips for many reasons, including:

Restoring a previous lip size. As you age, your lips may get smaller or thinner, your philtrum (the groove between your upper lip and septum) may get longer and flatter and the distance between the corners of your mouth (intercommissural distance) may increase.

Correcting the shape of your lips. It’s common for your lips to be different sizes or shapes (asymmetrical).

Smoothing wrinkles. When you smile or laugh, wrinkles sometimes develop on the sides of your mouth.

Fresh, glowing skin is a desire that many of us harbor, yearning to achieve that youthful and vibrant complexion.

While genetics and age play a significant role in our skin’s appearance, taking care of it through regular skin treatments can make all the difference. With the right approach, you can unlock the secrets to maintaining healthy, radiant skin.

One of the fundamental steps to achieving fresh skin is establishing a consistent skincare routine. Cleansing is essential to remove dirt, oil, and environmental pollutants that accumulate on our skin throughout the
day.

Exfoliation is another crucial aspect of skin treatment. This process helps eliminate dead skin cells, promoting cell turnover and revealing the new, radiant skin beneath. 
A mild exfoliator can gently slough away dead cells and encourage a healthy glow without causing irritation.

Regular moisturization should not be undermined when it comes to fresh skin. Moisturizers help to lock in hydration, preventing dryness and maintaining a soft, supple texture.

To enhance the efficacy of your skincare routine, consider incorporating serums or treatment products specific to your skin concerns. These targeted formulations can address issues like hyperpigmentation, acne, or fine lines, providing a boost of active ingredients that work to improve overall skin health.

Don’t forget the importance of protection from harmful UV rays.
Applying and reapplying broad-spectrum sunscreen with a high SPF helps shield the skin from damaging sun exposure.

Platelet rich plasma during and immediately post treatment

Plasma is the liquid portion of whole blood. It is composed largely of water and proteins, and it provides a medium for red blood cells, white blood cells and platelets to circulate through the body. Platelets, also called thrombocytes, are blood cells that cause blood clots, as well as other necessary growth and healing functions.

The activation of the concentrated platelets in platelet-rich plasma releases growth factors that stimulate and increase the number of reparative cells your body produces. This significantly enhances the body’s natural healing process.
Here, it does wonders for your skin.
